––– comment –––
ConversationalRag Plugin: Intent Classification, Expansion, and Exclusion Tests
Tests the core conversational features of the plugin using 3-level validation:
Structure: response contains required fields (conversation_uuid, response, sources)
Retrieval Quality: KNN returns correct category, negative checks (no wrong category),
groundedness (response mentions terms from source documents)
Pipeline Mechanics: log validation verifies that internal mechanisms run
(intent classifier, expansion calculator, exclusion handler) without asserting
specific LLM decisions which are non-deterministic
Based on issue #3978 and PR #625 (manticoresearch-buddy)
––– input –––
export SEARCHD_FLAGS="--logdebugvv"
––– output –––
––– block: ../base/start-searchd-with-buddy –––
––– comment –––
Setup: Create test table with 15 documents across 3 categories (AI, Entertainment, Programming)
Rich content for reliable KNN separation by topic
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS docs;"
––– output –––
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 << EOF
CREATE TABLE docs (
    id BIGINT,
    content TEXT,
    title TEXT,
    category TEXT,
    embedding_vector FLOAT_VECTOR
    knn_type='hnsw'
    hnsw_similarity='cosine'
    model_name='sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2'
    from='content,title'
    api_key='\${OPENAI_API_KEY}'
) TYPE='rt';
EOF
––– output –––
––– comment –––
Insert 15 test documents: AI (5), Entertainment (5), Programming (5)
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 << 'EOF'
INSERT INTO docs (id, content, title, category) VALUES
(1, 'Retrieval-Augmented Generation is a technique that combines information retrieval with large language models. RAG systems first search a knowledge base for relevant documents, then use an LLM to generate answers grounded in the retrieved context. This approach reduces hallucinations and provides traceable sources.', 'RAG Technology Overview', 'AI'),
(2, 'Vector search uses mathematical embeddings to find semantically similar documents. Each document is converted into a high-dimensional vector, and similarity is computed using metrics like cosine distance. This enables finding conceptually related content even without exact keyword matches.', 'Vector Search and Embeddings', 'AI'),
(3, 'Neural networks are computational models inspired by biological brain structure. Deep learning networks with multiple layers can learn hierarchical representations of data. They power modern AI applications from image recognition to natural language understanding.', 'Neural Networks Fundamentals', 'AI'),
(4, 'Natural Language Processing enables computers to understand and generate human language. Modern NLP uses transformer architectures like BERT and GPT for tasks such as sentiment analysis, translation, and text summarization. These models are pre-trained on massive text corpora.', 'NLP and Language Models', 'AI'),
(5, 'Computer vision is a field of AI that trains computers to interpret visual information from images and videos. Applications include facial recognition, autonomous driving, medical imaging diagnosis, and object detection in surveillance systems.', 'Computer Vision Applications', 'AI'),
(6, 'Breaking Bad is a critically acclaimed television series about Walter White, a high school chemistry teacher diagnosed with terminal lung cancer. He partners with former student Jesse Pinkman to manufacture and sell methamphetamine. The show explores themes of morality, family, and the consequences of choices.', 'Breaking Bad TV Series', 'Entertainment'),
(7, 'The Mandalorian is a Star Wars television series following a lone bounty hunter named Din Djarin in the outer reaches of the galaxy. He discovers and protects a young alien called Grogu, also known as Baby Yoda. The show features epic space battles and explores Mandalorian warrior culture.', 'The Mandalorian Series', 'Entertainment'),
(8, 'Stranger Things is a science fiction horror series set in the 1980s in the fictional town of Hawkins, Indiana. A group of kids uncover secret government experiments and a parallel dimension called the Upside Down. The show blends supernatural mystery with nostalgic pop culture references.', 'Stranger Things Overview', 'Entertainment'),
(9, 'Game of Thrones is an epic fantasy series based on George R.R. Martin novels about noble families fighting for control of the Iron Throne. The show features dragons, political intrigue, betrayal, and massive battle sequences across the continents of Westeros and Essos.', 'Game of Thrones Summary', 'Entertainment'),
(10, 'The Office is a mockumentary sitcom depicting the everyday lives of office employees at the Dunder Mifflin paper company in Scranton, Pennsylvania. Michael Scott, the bumbling regional manager, creates awkward and hilarious situations. The show is known for its dry humor and relatable workplace dynamics.', 'The Office Comedy Series', 'Entertainment'),
(11, 'Python is a high-level interpreted programming language known for its clean syntax and readability. It is widely used in web development with Django and Flask frameworks, data science with pandas and NumPy, and machine learning with TensorFlow and PyTorch libraries.', 'Python Programming Language', 'Programming'),
(12, 'JavaScript is the primary language for web development, running in browsers and on servers via Node.js. It supports event-driven programming, closures, and prototype-based object orientation. Modern JavaScript uses ES6+ features like arrow functions, async/await, and destructuring.', 'JavaScript Web Development', 'Programming'),
(13, 'Rust is a systems programming language focused on safety, speed, and concurrency without a garbage collector. Its ownership model prevents memory leaks and data races at compile time. Rust is popular for building high-performance web servers, embedded systems, and command-line tools.', 'Rust Systems Programming', 'Programming'),
(14, 'Go, also known as Golang, is a statically typed language developed by Google for building scalable network services and cloud infrastructure. It features built-in concurrency with goroutines and channels, fast compilation, and a comprehensive standard library for HTTP servers and microservices.', 'Go Language for Cloud', 'Programming'),
(15, 'Docker is a containerization platform that packages applications and their dependencies into lightweight, portable containers. Containers ensure consistent behavior across development, testing, and production environments. Docker Compose orchestrates multi-container applications with simple YAML configuration files.', 'Docker Containerization', 'Programming');
EOF
––– output –––
