Create RAG model for all tests
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CREATE RAG MODEL test_assistant (llm_provider='openai', llm_model='gpt-4o-mini');"
––– output –––
+--------------------------------------+
| uuid                                 |
+--------------------------------------+
| #!/[0-9a-z]{8}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{4}-[0-9a-z]{12}/!# |
+--------------------------------------+
––– comment –––
==========================================================================
CONVERSATION A: Multi-turn Conversation Flow (conv-intent-001)
Tests retrieval quality across topic transitions:
  A1: AI query → AI sources
  A2: Stay on AI → AI sources retained
  A3: Rejection → plugin still responds
  A4: Topic switch → Entertainment sources, AI not dominant
  A5: More options → Entertainment sources
Log checks verify pipeline mechanics (classifier runs, expansion state).
==========================================================================
––– comment –––
Test A1: Initial query about RAG
Retrieval: AI category | Groundedness: response mentions RAG terms
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('What is RAG and how does it work?', 'docs', 'test_assistant', 'content,title', 'conv-intent-001')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_a1.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: conv-intent-001
         response: #!/.*(RAG|[Rr]etrieval|[Aa]ugmented|[Gg]eneration).*/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Retrieval check A1: sources contain AI category
––– input –––
grep -c '"category":"AI"' /tmp/rag_a1.txt
––– output –––
#!/[1-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Pipeline check A1: intent classifier ran and produced a result
––– input –––
grep 'Detected intent' /var/log/manticore/searchd.log | tail -1
––– output –––
#!/.*Detected intent: [A-Z_]+.*/!#
––– comment –––
Pipeline check A1: expansion mechanism ran — NO on first query (deterministic: no prior results)
––– input –––
grep 'Expansion: NO' /var/log/manticore/searchd.log | tail -1
––– output –––
#!/.*Expansion: NO.*/!#
––– comment –––
Test A2: User shows interest in AI topic
Retrieval: AI category retained | Groundedness: response mentions AI terms
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('That sounds interesting, tell me more about AI', 'docs', 'test_assistant', 'content,title', 'conv-intent-001')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_a2.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: conv-intent-001
         response: #!/.*(AI|[Aa]rtificial|[Mm]achine|[Ll]earn|[Nn]eural|[Nn]etwork|[Vv]ector|NLP|[Ll]anguage).*/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Retrieval check A2: sources still contain AI category
––– input –––
grep -c '"category":"AI"' /tmp/rag_a2.txt
––– output –––
#!/[1-9][0-9]*/!#
––– comment –––
Pipeline check A2: intent classifier ran
––– input –––
grep 'Detected intent' /var/log/manticore/searchd.log | tail -1
––– output –––
#!/.*Detected intent: [A-Z_]+.*/!#
––– comment –––
Test A3: User rejects current topic
Structure: plugin responds without error
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Its boring, I dont like this topic', 'docs', 'test_assistant', 'content,title', 'conv-intent-001')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_a3.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
––– output –––
conversation_uuid: conv-intent-001
         response: #!/.+/!#
          sources: #!/\[.*/!#
––– comment –––
Pipeline check A3: intent classifier ran
––– input –––
grep 'Detected intent' /var/log/manticore/searchd.log | tail -1
––– output –––
#!/.*Detected intent: [A-Z_]+.*/!#
––– comment –––
Test A4: Topic switch from AI to Entertainment
Retrieval: Entertainment sources | Negative: NO AI sources | Groundedness: mentions shows
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "CALL CONVERSATIONAL_RAG('Tell me about TV shows instead', 'docs', 'test_assistant', 'content,title', 'conv-intent-001')\G" | tee /tmp/rag_a4.txt | grep -E "conversation_uuid:|response:|sources:"
